The paper deals with graph representations and visibility, which are topics commonly studied in computational geometry (cs.CG) and graph theory (cs.DS). The use of special shapes such as L, T, E, and H-shapes also suggests a possible connection to combinatorial optimization (cs.DM) and graph drawing (cs.GT). Finally, the mention of linear time algorithms and computational complexity hints at a potential application in algorithms and data structures (cs.SI).
